	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's best to think of color #0 as its own plane. It's a solid color plane, that you can do vertical gradients on - if you've got the interrupts for. But just remember, nothing is shown <em>behind</em> that plane <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />
<br />
<br /> And the 4 layers would be (from back to front):
<br />
<br /> BG #0, sprite low priority, BG tilemap, sprite high priority.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


